  overviewTitle="Block cavities before they start."
  overviewText="The chewing surfaces of molars are covered in deep pits and fissures — narrow grooves that are impossible to clean thoroughly with a toothbrush. Bacteria and food debris collect in these grooves and produce the acid that causes cavities. A dental sealant fills those grooves with a thin coating of resin, creating a smooth surface that is easy to clean and impermeable to bacterial acid. Studies show sealants reduce cavity risk in treated teeth by up to 80% — making them one of the most effective preventive treatments available."
  overviewExtra="Thrive Dental applies sealants to children's permanent molars as they erupt — typically around ages 6 and 12 — as a routine part of our preventive care program for families in Bayside, Whitestone, Fresh Meadows, and Little Neck. We also apply sealants to adults whose molars show no decay and no existing restorations, because the cavity-prevention logic is the same regardless of age. The procedure takes 5–10 minutes, requires no anesthesia, no drilling, and no recovery time. Sealants are one of the most cost-effective dental treatments available: the cost of a sealant is a fraction of the cost of one filling — and it prevents the cavity that would have required it."
